$section Linking to Specific Frame in XHTML$$

$head Discussion$$
OMhelp was using the $code name$$ attribute to 
target a specific frame for a link.
It turns out that the XHTML standard does not support this;
see
$href%
	http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/#h-4.10%
	4.10. The elements with 'id' and 'name' attributes
%$$  
OMhelp now follows the suggestion in
$href%
	http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/#C_8%
	C.8. Fragment Identifiers
%$$
and sets both the $code name$$ and $code id$$ attributes together;
e.g., 
$codep
	<a id="foo" name="foo">...</a>
$$
The result is that the links below now work properly.


